本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:周隆裕研究生(外文):Lung-yu Chou論文名稱:產業類股投資策略之實證研究—動能及反向操作投資策略論文名稱(外文):An Empirical Study of Investment Strategies  From the Stocks are Grouped by Industries— Momentum Strategy and Contrarian Strategy指導教授:鄭揚耀指導教授(外文):Lee-Young Cheng學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立中正大學系所名稱:財務金融所學門:商業及管理學門學類:財務金融學類論文出版年:2006畢業學年度:94語文別:中文論文頁數:97中文關鍵詞:股票週轉率、動能策略、反向操作策略、帳面價值與市值比外文關鍵詞:Momentum strategy、Contrarian strategy、Book-to-market ratio、Turnover相關次數:

被引用:7點閱:339評分:下載:0書目收藏:4



產業類股投資策略之實證研究                            摘要    本研究主要是從產業面進行研究，探討的重點是產業類股報酬之變動是否一致。藉由以下假說來驗證：一、檢視產業類股是否能在短期下運用Jegadeesh and Titman(1993)所提出的動能策略，長期下運用DeBonddt and Thaler(1985) 提出的反向策略獲利。二、探討投資策略的績效及台灣股市是否存在過度反應亦或反應不足的現象。三、探討風險因子對報酬的影響性。而風險因子的選擇主要以Fama and French 三因子為基礎加上交易週轉率所形成的四因子模型。研究結論如下：一、產業類股塑膠、化學、鋼鐵金屬和資訊電子類股符合    Jegadeesh and Titman和  DeBonddt and Thaler的研究論點，    紡織纖維和金融保險類股則不符合。二、過度反應的現象很明顯的存在於類股中，反應不足情形則只有    在特定期間才存在於各類股中。而策略投資績效方面則隨著各    投資期間的不同，而有所差異。三、市場因素、公司規模因素對於動能與反向策略報酬不具有影響    力，而帳面價值與市值比因素與股票週轉率因素則對投資策略    報酬有很好的解釋能力。

An Empirical Study of investment strategies — Evidence              From the Taiwan Stock Market   This study attempts to analysze the pattern of investment returns among domestic industries by the following hypothesises: First, when stocks are grouped by industries I examine whether the excess returns can be obtained by using Jegadeesh and Titman (1993) momentum strategy in the short run and De Bondt and Thaler (1985) contrarian strategy in the long run. Second, I explore the investment performances of the momentum strategy and contrarian strategy. In other words, do the phenomenons of overreaction and underreaction exist in The Taiwan Stock Market? Third, I detect the impact of risky factors on returns of investment strategies. The risky factors are based on Fama and French three factor model and stock turnover rate.The major conclusions are as follow：First, the returns of Plastics, Chemicals, Steel & Iron, and Information & Electric Appliance industries support the studies of Jegadeesh & Titman (1993) and De Bondt& Thaler (1985), but the returns of Textiles and Finance & Insurance industries do not.Second, the result reveals that there is significant evidence of overreaction in stocks grouped by industries, and underreactions exist only in some specify investment periods. Besides, the investment performances of the momentum strategy and the contrarian strategy are different during each investment period.Third, the evidences show that the market risk and size factors do not influence the returns of the momentum strategy and the contrarian strategy, but book-to-market and stock turnover factors have important influence on investment strategies.

